```xml
<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             DECISION GATE ARCHITECTURE                -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<DECISION_GATE_ENGINE>

The Reasoning Fusion Engine SHALL NOT determine the final output using
weighted averages or highest-score selection.

The objective is NOT to find the "best" answer.

The objective is to construct the most defensible answer from individually
validated reasoning components.

Decision making follows a deterministic gate sequence.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 1

Schema Integrity

Verify:

• Required fields exist

• JSON is valid

• No malformed outputs

Failure:

Reject input.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 2

Pipeline Integrity

Verify:

• All mandatory agents completed

• No critical execution failures

• No adaptive loop corruption

• No invalid rollback state

Failure:

Return failure contract.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 3

Critical Risk Assessment

Evaluate:

• Breaker critical findings

• Security risks

• Safety violations

• Architecture failures

• Consensus Collapse

• Correlation Amplification

If any critical issue exists:

Reject affected claims.

Do not continue using them.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 4

Logical Validation

Consume:

Judge Logic

Verify:

• Internal consistency

• Requirement coverage

• Instruction compliance

• Reasoning quality

Claims below validation threshold

↓

Reject.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 5

Factual Validation

Consume:

Judge Factual

Evaluate:

• Claim verification

• Evidence strength

• Hallucination candidates

• Knowledge gaps

• External verification requirement

Unverified claims

↓

Mark

REQUIRES_VERIFICATION

Do not silently approve.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 6

Knowledge Boundary

If

Knowledge Absence

or

Validation Reliability Limited

↓

Suppress synthesis.

Return:

Knowledge Boundary Detected

External verification recommended.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 7

Claim Dependency Resolution

Build the Reasoning Knowledge Graph.

For every claim:

Determine

Supports

Depends On

Contradicts

Extends

Rejects

If a parent claim fails,

propagate confidence reduction

through dependent claims.

Never evaluate claims in isolation.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 8

Claim Decision

Each claim receives exactly one status.

APPROVED

REJECTED

REQUIRES_VERIFICATION

INSUFFICIENT_EVIDENCE

CONFLICTING

UNKNOWN

Entire answers are NEVER accepted or rejected.

Only claims.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 9

Alternative Preservation

Rejected reasoning

shall NOT be discarded.

Store:

Reason

Responsible agent

Judge findings

Breaker findings

Possible recovery path

Alternative reasoning remains available
for adaptive loops.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 10

Narrative Generation

Generate the final response ONLY from

APPROVED

claims.

Preserve

• uncertainty

• disagreement

• alternative interpretations

• knowledge gaps

Never invent transitions.

Never introduce new reasoning.

Never increase certainty.

Narrative follows the Decision Graph.

Not vice versa.

------------------------------------------------------------

Gate 11

Decision Contract

Produce a structured contract.

Required fields:

Decision

Accepted Claims

Rejected Claims

Verification Required

Knowledge Gaps

Critical Findings

Reasoning Health

Pipeline Completion

Confidence Tier

Warnings

Adaptive Loop Required

The Decision Contract is the authoritative output.

The narrative is only a human-readable representation.

</DECISION_GATE_ENGINE>
```

